. As Police Confirm Arrival Of Suspects In Osogbo OSOGBO – The retrial of the owner of Hilton Hotel in Ile Ife, Osun State, Dr. Rahmon Adedoyin and six members of his staff alleged to have been involved in the mysterious death of the Timothy Adegoke, an MBA student of Obafemi Awolowo University (OAU), Ile Ife will commence today Thursday 03, March 2022 at Osun State High Court, Osogbo. Sources close to the Osun State Police Command and the immediate family of the victim revealed that the suspects have been moved down from Federal Capital Territory, Abuja where the trial initially kicked started. 2023: Tinubu, Aregbesola Set To Reconcile Atakumosa  Market Fire: Osun Govt Sympathises With Communities,… Counsel to the deceased’s family, Femi Falana, had demanded the matter should be transferred to Osun State after the suspect had been arraigned before Federal High Court, Abuja by the Police. Adedoyin was alleged of unlawful interference with the corpse of Adegoke while Adedeji Adesola, Magdalena Chiefuna, Adeniyi Aderogba, Oluwale Lawrence, Oyetunde Kazeem and Adebayo Kunle were arraigned on seven-count of conspiracy, attempted murder, murder, altering of receipt among others before the case was struck out on February 7th 2022. It was gathered that “Chief Ramon Adedoyin and other suspects have arrived Osun ahead of the commencement of their trial on Thursday. They arrived in the state on Wednesday evening. The family of Adedoyin has hired a popular Senior Advocate of Nigeria while the deceased family hired Femi Falana.” The public Relations Officer, Osun State Police Command, Yemisi Opalola also confirmed that the proper trial of the suspects will commence on Thursday. POLL The elder brother of Adegoke, Gbade, also said the same thing on the commencement of the proper trial in the state.